# Tile

Tiles and rasters

from vega_datasets import data

data = data.windvectors()
data
longitude latitude dir dirCat speed
0 0.125 45.125 228 225 3.12
1 0.375 45.125 228 225 3.24
2 0.625 45.125 229 225 3.34
3 0.875 45.125 229 225 3.44
4 1.125 45.125 228 225 3.48
... ... ... ... ... ...
4795 -1.125 59.875 155 150 5.96
4796 -0.875 59.875 154 150 6.34
4797 -0.625 59.875 153 150 6.71
4798 -0.375 59.875 152 150 7.09
4799 -0.125 59.875 152 150 7.48

4800 rows × 5 columns

ggplot() + geom_point(data=data, mapping=aes(x='longitude', y='latitude', color='speed')) + ggsize(1000, 800) \
    + scale_color_cmapmpl('RdBu', trans='reverse')
ggplot() + geom_tile(data=data, mapping=aes(x='longitude', y='latitude', fill='speed')) + ggsize(1000, 800) \
    + scale_fill_cmapmpl('RdBu', trans='reverse')
ggplot() + geom_raster(data=data, mapping=aes(x='longitude', y='latitude', fill='speed')) + ggsize(1000, 800) \
    + scale_fill_cmapmpl('Reds')
# 2-D Histograms

2-D Histograms

from vega_datasets import data

data = data.movies()
data = data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating', 'Major_Genre']].dropna()
data
Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating IMDB_Rating Major_Genre
4 62.0 3.4 Drama
11 84.0 7.5 Musical
21 57.0 7.0 Drama
22 33.0 5.6 Comedy
28 77.0 7.1 Drama
... ... ... ...
3195 89.0 7.8 Comedy
3196 65.0 7.0 Comedy
3198 3.0 3.4 Adventure
3199 26.0 5.7 Adventure
3200 82.0 6.7 Adventure

2131 rows × 3 columns

ggplot() + geom_point(data=data, mapping=aes(x='IMDB_Rating', y='Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', color='Major_Genre')) + ggsize(800, 600)
ggplot() + geom_bin2d(data=data, mapping=aes(x='IMDB_Rating', y='Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'), bins=[20, 20]) + ggsize(800, 600) + coord_cartesian() \
    + scale_fill_cmapmpl('Spectral', trans='reverse')
ggplot() + geom_density2df(data=data, mapping=aes(x='IMDB_Rating', y='Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', fill='..level..'), bins=20, show_legend=True, bw=2) + scale_fill_brewer('div', palette='Spectral', direction=-1)  + coord_cartesian()
